## Description
The **Archive Receipts (LEA) **task allows to load receipts into the Doxee Platform 2 Legal Electronic Archiving (LEA) software service.

> Note

For more information, see: [How to Connect a DP3 Application to a LEA Environment via Authorization Key.](https://code.doxee.com/confluence/display/DS/How%2Bto%2BConnect%2Ba%2BDP3%2BApplication%2Bto%2Ba%2BLEA%2BEnvironment%2Bvia%2BAuthorization%2BKey)  

> Important

This feature is only available on Milan tenants.

## Configuration
![](data:image/png;base64,)

- In the **Alias **field, enter the name of the task that will be displayed in the workflow.

- In the **Authorization tag **field, enter the unique LEA authorization tag.

> Note

For more information, see: [Legal Electronic Archiving - Manuali Utente](https://code.doxee.com/confluence/display/DD/Legal%2BElectronic%2BArchiving%2B-%2BManuali%2BUtente).

- *(optional) *Enable the **Manual approval **option to request manual approval of the job.

> Note

For more information, see: [Doxee Platform Batch Jobs - Managing Jobs](/doxee-platform/docs/doxee-platform-batch-jobs-managing-jobs).

#### Rep file
The *testPdV*.rep *file contains the task's output; for example:

**Example: Rep file**

`In data 13/09/2023 alle ore 16:17:15 il pacchetto di versamento testPdV-2023-09-13-17-05-02-544 con ID P1694617502542 relativo al titolare dei ricevute NOME TITOLARE (Codice PRODUCTDEVELOPMENT) e' stato preso in carico e il contenuto e' stato caricato per poter procedere alle fasi successive del servizio di conservazione digitale.
Di seguito i dettagli:
TIPOLOGIA DOCUMENTALE | NUMERO DOCUMENTI CARICATI FATTURE | 10`#### LEA Loader logs
The *lea_loader*.log *file provides detailed information on the LEA Loader execution.

> **Note for internal users**

For more information, see: [[LEA-LOADER] Come analizzare un job batch in stop sul task LEA-LOADER](https://code.doxee.com/confluence/display/SP/%2B%2B%5BLEA-LOADER%5D%2BCome%2Banalizzare%2Bun%2Bjob%2Bbatch%2Bin%2Bstop%2Bsul%2Btask%2BLEA-LOADER).

#### Report logs
The files in the *report *folder are useful in case of problems with the database query, for example if a value is too large for LEA tables.
